Beat: 1 November 2010 Time: 52:04

Every time reviewers call a game hard, long, and involved I shy away from it. But as I've played more games I've realized that I've played a ton of hard, long, and complex games in my life. And the worse thing is of all that I end up loving them!

My first contact with Final Fantasy Tactics was with the PSX original. I thought it was awesome. The map, the strategies involved, the way it looked stayed in my mind. I didn't even tried it, I don't think my brother ever finished it either. So as soon as I saw the game at Best Buy I grabbed, it was an impulse buy I'm glad I bought it. 
I was too dumb to understand the plot but the game play was all I needed. Yasumi Matsuno really knows his stuff. I'm this close to break out my PS2 copy of Final Fantasy XII or actually finish Vagrant Story. The world of Ivalice is wonderful, isn't it?

I usually do a lot research before I commit to a game. Having had Final Fantasy Tactics and the Devil Survivor games under my belt, I felt more at ease with strategy games. 
I had downloaded Ogre Battle 64 on the Wii and I was familiar with Yasumi Matsuno work at that point so when this port was announced and later released I wanted it but I was too chicken to get it. 
Sometimes you want to play nice games that won't force you out of your coziness. But sometimes you need to jump into the vision of a developer and sit down for the lesson. 
What a game! The sad thing about it is that I missed on Ogre Battle: March of the Black Queen on the Wii Virtual Console and there's no way I'm buy the PSX or SNES version. 
I can take confort in Let Us Cling Together though. What a ride!

The Overwatch Grand Finals day has finally arrived and passed by, but not without meeting a bunch of amazing people! I got to take pictures and talk to so many people just as passionate about the game as I am. I'm truly floored by how nice everyone was! I even got to have the pleasure of meeting the owner of the Hangzhou Spark who was incredibly excited to see my cosplay! Getting to be a #sponsored cosplayer again this year for the finals was an amazing opportunity and I'd LOVE to return again. Thank you to @stephenvhuynh for helping make this possible, thank you to my boyfriend for making the day go by smoothly, and thank you to everyone for the birthday gift of a lifetime and for making my day special.
.
.

⠀
Várias escolas e instituições ao redor do mundo já se utilizam do jogo para ajudar no ensino de disciplinas como matemática e geografia, pois #Minecraft traz muitas possibilidades com o seu mundo aberto e a liberdade de criação. Além desses aspectos, o jogo também estimula a criatividade, o desenvolvimento cognitivo, senso de cooperação e responsabilidade. ⠀
⠀
Aliar jogos ao aprendizado pode ser uma forma muito interessante de despertar o interesse dos alunos, quem disse que não pode aprender brincando? 🎮💻⠀

Beat: 21 September 2010 Time: 10:48

I'm always on the lookout for cool and strange games. I'm one of those cheap bastards who waits for AAA popular titles to drop to 5 cents. But when it comes to smaller weird games I pay full price. 
During 2008-2010 Xseed was publishing very cool titles and Half-Minute Hero looked and played like nothing before. 
It's a great game for short bursts. It makes me happy thinking about it. 
It's a hidden gem for you PSP and handheld gamers!

Beat: 21 August 2010 Time: 27:11

I don't subscribe to the notion that the 16-and 32-bit eras have the best JRPGs. For my JRPG fix I go to the PS2/GCN/PSP/DS/3DS eras. Having said that, there's a ton of games from the PSX days that I missed out on but I'm starting to get around them. 
I remember holding the first Lunar in my hand in the late 90s. The game was super expensive and it even got more expensive when collectors took it away from gamers. 
But the game remained in my mind and thankfully I got a chance to play the remake on the PSP. I remember little but the graphics were beautiful. The voice acting, well, probably some people find it charming. 
I think I understand why people love that series. I'm sad that it didn't click with me but I still think it's a cool game.

Ya estamos cada vez más cerca de poder jugar los nuevos juegos de Pokémon, pero queremos aprovechar y mostrarles un poco de cada una de las criaturas previamente anunciadas.

Desliza para conocerlas.

#HechoPorFanaticos #Pokemon #PokemonSword #PokemonShield #Nintendo

Según Deadline, El nuevo acuerdo consiste en que Disney/Marvel Studios co-financiarán 25% del presupuesto de la nueva cinta por recibir el 25% de lo recaudado en taquilla. Sony además recibirá 8% o tal vez más por la distribución de la película.

Algo importante es que el regreso de Tom Holland al mundo cinematográfico de la Casa de Ideas es que Kevin Feige, presidente de Marvel Studios, seguirá formando parte del proceso creativo del nuevo film junto con Amy Pascal, expresidenta de Sony y ahora líder de su propio estudio, Pascal Pictures.

La nueva cinta de Spider-Man con solo Tom Holland confirmado hasta ahora, estará en cines el 16 de julio del 2021, un mes después de Doctor Strange Into de Multiverse of Madness y meses antes de Thor: Love and Thunder.

Claramente la evaluación del contrato pudo haber sido influenciado tanto por la respuesta de los fans, como también de como ambas compañías podían integrar tanto la presencia como falta de uno de los héroes más populares del mundo, ahora interpretado a la perfección por Holland.

Brutal Mario (鬼畜王マリオ Kichiku Ou Mario, Brutal King Mario), also known as Super Kitiku Mario, is a Super Mario World ROM hack created by a mysterious Japanese ROM-hacker who goes by the name of Carol.

It's well known for being a hack with a large amount of custom bosses and ASM gimmicks, with its development being started when such things were but a dream in the SMW hacking scene.

The hack contains several references to many other video games, from Final Fantasy, to Twinbee, to Kirby, to Mega Man, to even Cho Aniki of all things. (Source brutalmario.fandom.com)

caption.text:
There are some historically amazing boss fight transformations for Super Nintendo games.

And the Mother Brain second form is definitely one of them!

After destroying the barriers, breaking the glass container, and shooting Mother Brain with a bunch of missiles, it transforms into a freaking dinosaur!

How awesome was this when you first played it?! Were you amazed, terrified, or somewhere in-between when you saw this second form??
